# Desktop Presence Foundation (Phase 25)

Read **[DESKTOP_PRESENCE_FOUNDATION.md](../../DESKTOP_PRESENCE_FOUNDATION.md)** before changes to notifications, quiet hours, or desktop APIs.

## Layer ownership (mandatory before implementation)

| Surface | Owner |
|---------|-------|
| Notification UI, preferences, `/app/presence` | **Customer App** |
| Delivery APIs, quiet-hours logic, personality templates | **Shared** (`lib/presence/`) |
| Unonight pilot metrics | **Platform Admin** |

## Rules

1. Native desktop client is Phase 27 (`apps/command-center/`) — this phase covers notification infrastructure only
2. Notification levels: informational → important → action_required → critical
3. Users must control preferences — quiet hours, channels, minimum levels
4. Critical alerts may bypass quiet hours; vacation mode suppresses non-essential noise
5. Professional tone — no enthusiasm spam (`lib/presence/personality.ts`)
6. Actionable notifications support view, approve, open dashboard, dismiss, escalate
7. Never store email content, chat, or PII in notification payloads
8. Extend Phase 13 Presence Center — do not replace `PresenceProvider` without migration plan
9. Desktop clients register in `presence_desktop_clients` when apps ship — not before

> Aipify should feel present. Not intrusive.
